<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lamentable" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lamentable,</orth> 1) to be lamented, pitiful, causing pity or sorrow: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 15, 52</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 15, 52</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.273" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 273</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.125" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 1, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.85" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 85</bibl>.<lb />2) pertaining to grief, expressing sorrow: <emph>that l. rheum</emph> (viz tears) <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 22</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>